03:18.616 --> 03:19.909
Well, I can't thank you enough

03:20.076 --> 03:22.245
for arranging this
on such short notice.

03:22.412 --> 03:23.705
At times like these,

03:23.872 --> 03:25.748
we have to move quickly
and stick together.

03:25.915 --> 03:27.709
So true.

03:27.876 --> 03:30.003
Well, I've climbed
Mt Everest twice,

03:30.169 --> 03:32.338
and that's not something
one does on one's own.

03:32.505 --> 03:34.215
Beating this disease is...

03:34.382 --> 03:36.217
..it's an even taller mountain
to climb.

03:36.384 --> 03:39.596
Well, think of Godfrey as
the Sherpa on whose back, um...

03:39.762 --> 03:43.141
..Hillary...somebody
rode to Everest's summit.

03:43.308 --> 03:44.434
Huh.

03:44.601 --> 03:48.980
Well, Sir Edmund didn't actually
ride on Tenzing Norgay's back.

03:49.147 --> 03:51.900
Well, however he got there,
we'll be right there with you.

03:52.066 --> 03:53.192
Right.

03:56.905 --> 03:58.531
Norville Knox.

04:00.325 --> 04:02.744
Godfrey's very own Tenha Norway.

04:02.911 --> 04:06.331
Dr Johann Pryce, of course.
I'm an aficionado of your work.

04:06.497 --> 04:08.416
Your paper
on glycosylated haemoglobin

04:08.583 --> 04:11.210
led to some delicious advances
by my own team.

04:11.377 --> 04:13.630
It is an absolute honour
to meet you, sir.

04:13.796 --> 04:15.131
May I congratulate you

04:15.298 --> 04:17.382
for having utterly
transmogrified philanthropy

04:17.550 --> 04:19.302
from a guilt-driven hobby
of the privileged

04:19.469 --> 04:21.471
to a dynamic
and transformative tool

04:21.637 --> 04:23.097
that, when systematically
deployed

04:23.264 --> 04:25.516
as you have done with
such insight and discipline,

04:25.683 --> 04:28.645
has activated and energised
the scientific community

04:28.811 --> 04:30.897
to levels of discovery
and innovation

04:31.064 --> 04:32.440
never thought possible.

04:32.607 --> 04:34.233
Why don't you just blow the guy?

04:34.400 --> 04:36.778
At least a dick
in his obsequious little mouth

04:36.945 --> 04:38.780
would shut him up.

04:39.948 --> 04:40.949
What?

04:41.115 --> 04:43.242
Well, I'm delighted
that a man of your stature

04:43.409 --> 04:45.578
is just looking
into this wretched disease.

04:45.745 --> 04:48.831
- Now, is Dr Pryce...
- Upir? No.

04:48.998 --> 04:50.750
Though the body count
he's racked up

04:50.917 --> 04:52.710
beats both of ours, combined.

04:52.877 --> 04:54.837
In the name of science,
of course.

04:57.298 --> 04:58.925
Uh, may I?

04:59.092 --> 05:01.010
Yes, please. By all means.

05:02.595 --> 05:04.764
I'll ask you to keep the fawning
to a minimum

05:04.931 --> 05:07.016
when it's me in that body.

05:07.183 --> 05:09.477
No. You're not planning... Him?

05:09.644 --> 05:12.438
Handsome? Check. Upir? Check.
Rich? Double check.

05:12.605 --> 05:14.941
When you called, you said he was
coming to help. I thought...

05:15.108 --> 05:16.776
I was sitting next to him
on his plane.

05:16.943 --> 05:18.403
What else was I supposed to say?

05:18.569 --> 05:20.738
If we wipe his brain, it'll
destroy everything I believe in.

05:20.905 --> 05:22.615
So it's a short list, then.

05:22.782 --> 05:24.200
This man is responsible

05:24.367 --> 05:25.785
for shaping the future
of our civilisation

05:25.952 --> 05:27.662
through his patronage
to science.

05:27.829 --> 05:31.249
And yet, somehow that future
never seemed to include you.

05:31.416 --> 05:33.334
No. I have access
to the Godfrey funds.

05:33.501 --> 05:35.253
The White Tower.
I want for nothing.

05:35.420 --> 05:36.754
Use your imagination.

05:36.921 --> 05:38.715
His resources. His facilities.

05:38.881 --> 05:40.633
They could all be ours.

05:41.843 --> 05:43.469
Well, yours.

05:44.804 --> 05:46.764
Or I'll just feast on him.

05:47.890 --> 05:49.267
The scientific community

05:49.434 --> 05:51.269
will crumble
without his largesse,

05:51.436 --> 05:53.271
I will die
without a surrogate body,

05:53.438 --> 05:56.149
and your demonic perversions
masquerading as science

05:56.315 --> 05:59.193
will be exposed
for the whole world to see.

06:01.612 --> 06:04.157
Impressive discovery,
Pryce.

06:04.323 --> 06:05.992
With our combined resources,

06:06.159 --> 06:08.953
this thing doesn't stand
a chance.

06:09.120 --> 06:10.663
Quite so.

06:11.664 --> 06:14.459
Uh. Ugh!

06:16.461 --> 06:18.087
Jesus, Johann!
Be a little more careful

06:18.254 --> 06:19.881
with my new body,
will you, please?

06:20.048 --> 06:22.842
It's not yours. Not yet.

06:23.009 --> 06:24.343
Certain threats were made

06:24.510 --> 06:25.887
about sharing the fruits
of my labour -

06:26.054 --> 06:27.388
'atrocities' I believe you
called them -

06:27.555 --> 06:28.848
with the authorities.

06:29.015 --> 06:31.392
I'm putting my life
in your bloody little hands.

06:31.559 --> 06:33.394
Some insurance is only prudent.

06:33.561 --> 06:34.854
When I'm certain you've held up

06:35.021 --> 06:36.856
your end of the bargain,
I won't need leverage.

06:37.023 --> 06:38.691
I'll perform the transfer.

06:38.858 --> 06:40.359
You turn over whatever
information you have.

06:40.526 --> 06:42.695
Do we have a deal?

06:42.862 --> 06:44.489
I need to hear you
say the words.

06:44.655 --> 06:48.117
Oh, for fuck's sake! You're
such a suspicious little prick.

06:49.577 --> 06:52.163
Yes, we have a deal.

07:10.223 --> 07:11.849
<i>This is your Destiny.</i>

07:12.016 --> 07:13.518
<i>I already know
why you're calling,</i>

07:13.684 --> 07:14.977
<i>but if you're feeling
redundant,</i>

07:15.144 --> 07:16.604
<i>state your need after the beep.</i>

07:27.698 --> 07:30.827
Dee? Honey? I got us breakfast.

07:30.993 --> 07:33.663
- She's not here.
- Where is she?

07:33.830 --> 07:35.873
She didn't come home last night.

07:36.040 --> 07:37.834
I thought maybe
she crashed at your place.

07:38.000 --> 07:39.627
Well, she didn't.

07:39.794 --> 07:41.462
Where could she be?

07:41.629 --> 07:43.714
After all the lies
you've been telling her,

07:43.881 --> 07:45.174
maybe she's on a bender.

07:45.341 --> 07:47.051
Destiny wouldn't do that.

07:49.095 --> 07:51.097
And I came here to tell her
the whole story.

07:51.264 --> 07:53.599
Which version?

07:53.766 --> 07:55.059
Bet your ass is covered,

07:55.226 --> 07:58.229
no matter what crock of shit
you and Baj are telling, anyway.

07:59.438 --> 08:01.190
I'm here every morning,

08:01.357 --> 08:04.610
and I watch her cry
until there's nothing left.

08:04.777 --> 08:07.280
I listen to her trying
to figure out how her cousin

08:07.446 --> 08:09.073
could break her heart like this.

08:09.240 --> 08:11.576
I'm there for her.

08:11.742 --> 08:13.870
And you?

08:14.036 --> 08:16.205
Ride or die?

08:16.372 --> 08:18.374
Go fuck yourself.

08:18.541 --> 08:19.876
I can't go back in time.

08:20.042 --> 08:22.128
I can only find her
and make things better.

08:22.295 --> 08:24.839
You want to know what Destiny
was like before you showed up?

08:25.006 --> 08:26.883
She was happy.

08:32.096 --> 08:33.931
And all you found out
about this cabin

08:34.097 --> 08:35.558
is that it's not
in Connecticut?

08:35.725 --> 08:38.394
With Spivak's connection
to Essex and Plum Island nearby,

08:38.561 --> 08:40.104
it seemed reasonable
to assume that...

08:40.270 --> 08:41.731
Quit your yammering.
You have nothing.

08:41.898 --> 08:43.191
I do not have nothing.

08:43.357 --> 08:45.526
I've a blinding headache
and a fucking facial tic

08:45.693 --> 08:47.987
from playing 'Where's Waldo'
for the last 37 hours straight.

08:48.154 --> 08:50.323
Do you think I give a fuck?

08:50.489 --> 08:51.908
If you can't find this place,

08:52.074 --> 08:54.702
I'll shitcan you myself
and find someone who can.

09:11.636 --> 09:13.221
You gonna kill me now?

09:17.767 --> 09:19.894
I'm not a murderer.

09:36.327 --> 09:39.789
Go on. Get it over with.

09:39.956 --> 09:42.124
I'll make it easy for you.

09:44.460 --> 09:46.337
I'm not a murderer.

09:50.424 --> 09:51.759
You saw what happened.

09:51.926 --> 09:53.552
She came in here
shrieking at me

09:53.719 --> 09:55.054
after I was almost gunned down.

09:55.221 --> 09:56.847
Then she hit me.

09:57.014 --> 09:58.975
And I shouldn't have
hit her back,

09:59.141 --> 10:00.601
but no way did I mean for...

10:00.768 --> 10:03.562
- What about after that?
- She was dying.

10:05.064 --> 10:06.649
If Peter saw her like that,

10:06.816 --> 10:09.527
it wouldn't have mattered
if it was an accident or not.

10:09.694 --> 10:12.863
He would have come after me
until one of us was dead.

10:13.030 --> 10:14.865
And he wouldn't have stopped
with just me.

10:15.032 --> 10:17.118
You were there, too.

10:17.285 --> 10:19.370
I didn't have a choice.

10:19.537 --> 10:21.372
You have to understand that.

10:24.250 --> 10:26.085
I understand, Roman.

10:27.086 --> 10:28.587
I do.

10:28.754 --> 10:31.173
I didn't mean to hurt anyone.

10:32.216 --> 10:33.384
But you did,

10:33.551 --> 10:36.220
and you'll have to learn
to live with that.

10:39.640 --> 10:42.518
I took many lives
when I was finding my way.

10:42.685 --> 10:46.230
It wasn't until I turned my life
over to the will of God

10:46.397 --> 10:49.191
that I was able
to accept myself...

10:50.818 --> 10:53.112
..in spite of what I'd done.

10:56.365 --> 10:57.825
Penance.

10:57.992 --> 10:59.368
Atonement.

10:59.535 --> 11:01.662
Forgiveness.

11:01.829 --> 11:03.664
These aren't just words.

11:03.831 --> 11:07.168
That shit doesn't work for me.

11:07.335 --> 11:10.171
A fucking priest man
told me so himself.

11:11.213 --> 11:13.174
I don't know
what this priest told you

11:13.341 --> 11:16.427
or what you think you heard,
but I do know this -

11:16.594 --> 11:20.014
"There are many rooms
in my father's house."

11:23.100 --> 11:24.935
Room for me?

11:25.936 --> 11:29.940
I'm 100% certain
there's no room at the inn.

11:34.028 --> 11:35.446
Fuck.

11:35.613 --> 11:37.448
Remember what happens
if he finds out.

11:37.615 --> 11:39.325
To him. To you.

11:45.915 --> 11:48.376
Destiny didn't come home
last night. Is she here?

11:48.542 --> 11:50.961
I haven't seen her
since the funeral.

11:51.128 --> 11:52.463
Please excuse me.

11:52.630 --> 11:56.300
Sorry I have to leave so soon
but I'm late for an appointment.

11:56.467 --> 11:59.261
What about you?
Did she reach out to you?

12:02.348 --> 12:04.141
No, she didn't.

12:10.439 --> 12:13.734
Destiny probably just needs
some space after all this.

12:13.901 --> 12:15.111
She'll turn up.

12:15.277 --> 12:17.905
Come on,
I got something to show you.

12:18.072 --> 12:20.658
- This was in Trevor's head?
- So was I.

12:21.951 --> 12:24.495
I saw all of it.
The cabin, Spivak, everything.

12:28.082 --> 12:31.252
- This is big.
- We're so close.

12:31.419 --> 12:33.546
We should head over
to the White Tower

12:33.712 --> 12:36.340
and keep the pressure on them
to find this place.

12:38.050 --> 12:40.261
I can't do anything
until I know where Destiny is.

12:40.428 --> 12:42.763
I gotta say,
I think you're overreacting.

12:42.930 --> 12:44.765
This is the break
we've been waiting for, Peter.

12:44.932 --> 12:48.018
I'm not gonna be any use to us
until I'm sure she's OK.

12:49.645 --> 12:51.564
What happened to your hand?

12:53.274 --> 12:55.484
The shooting in the boardroom.
I told you.

12:55.651 --> 12:58.112
Destiny's a grown-ass woman.
What are you so worried about?

12:58.279 --> 12:59.196
Everything.

12:59.363 --> 13:00.823
I'm worried
she went to the cops,

13:00.990 --> 13:02.658
and they're keeping her
on ice somewhere,

13:02.825 --> 13:04.160
or Milan got to her,

13:04.326 --> 13:06.036
and now Spivak's going around
lighting up on people.

13:06.203 --> 13:08.080
Who the fuck knows
what happened to her?

13:09.540 --> 13:12.126
She already went
after Milan once.

13:12.293 --> 13:14.837
If he gets a whiff that
I do not have her under control,

13:15.004 --> 13:16.630
she's gonna be fucked.

13:16.797 --> 13:19.800
So if she's planning on taking
another run at this prick...

13:19.967 --> 13:21.469
Yeah. What am I supposed to do?

13:21.635 --> 13:23.345
Ring his doorbell and say,
"Hey, by the way,

13:23.512 --> 13:25.181
"my cousin's gonna try
and murder you again,

13:25.347 --> 13:27.766
"in case you haven't
taken her out already."

13:30.394 --> 13:31.896
I have another approach.

14:05.638 --> 14:07.181
Have as much as you want.

14:07.348 --> 14:09.058
It's crabapple juice.

14:09.225 --> 14:11.310
Supposed to be
an anti-oxidant...

14:12.436 --> 14:14.355
..which, I guess,
is a good thing.

14:17.399 --> 14:18.692
I wasn't snooping.

14:18.859 --> 14:22.821
This palace is for the enjoyment
of all who enter within.

14:27.326 --> 14:28.869
Oh.

14:29.036 --> 14:31.830
I was worried about you.
Where have you been?

14:33.707 --> 14:36.752
I needed a think, a deep one,

14:36.919 --> 14:39.880
which I do best
when I'm by my lonesome

14:40.047 --> 14:44.843
and...when I have
my thinking cube.

14:45.010 --> 14:49.473
That's my re-imagining
of a cultural icon.

14:49.640 --> 14:53.143
Blue, symbolising, uh...

14:54.520 --> 14:55.563
..blue.

14:57.147 --> 14:59.358
What did you need
to think about?

15:00.985 --> 15:02.653
Butterflies.

15:03.904 --> 15:05.239
Butterflies?

15:05.406 --> 15:07.575
Hmm.

15:07.741 --> 15:09.201
The monarch butterfly

15:09.368 --> 15:11.579
congregates in May and
during the warmer months

15:11.745 --> 15:14.498
because of its fondness
for milkweed.

15:14.665 --> 15:18.752
I was thinking about hitting
the road, getting a look-see.

15:18.919 --> 15:22.256
Supposed to be a sight
so beautiful it moved God

15:22.423 --> 15:25.050
to invent the eyeball,
so we could see it.

15:25.217 --> 15:27.303
You're leaving?

15:27.469 --> 15:30.639
I was hoping to change that
to the first-person plural.

15:32.433 --> 15:36.103
The two of us.
Open road. Butterflies.

15:36.270 --> 15:38.856
We could leave tonight.

15:43.027 --> 15:45.362
I sense reluctance.

15:51.243 --> 15:53.454
They treat me bad enough
around here.

15:53.621 --> 15:56.373
Why would it be different
anywhere else?

15:56.540 --> 15:58.500
I'm a big freak.

15:58.667 --> 16:01.545
I believe it was Jimi Hendrix
who urged us

16:01.712 --> 16:04.256
to wave our freak flag high.

16:04.423 --> 16:06.800
You, being taller than most,

16:06.967 --> 16:10.054
are ideally suited
to do just that.

16:10.220 --> 16:12.473
It's time for you
to get out there.

16:12.640 --> 16:15.309
Go some of those places
you've only read about.

16:15.476 --> 16:17.019
I'd be honoured mightily

16:17.186 --> 16:19.063
if you'd have me
as your fellow traveller.

16:23.567 --> 16:25.277
Big decision.

16:25.444 --> 16:27.988
Yeah, as decisions go, probably.

16:31.075 --> 16:33.285
Which will require a think...

16:35.579 --> 16:37.081
..and this.

16:48.509 --> 16:50.094
Olivia.

16:51.095 --> 16:52.721
Olivia?

16:54.139 --> 16:57.017
Congratulations.
The transfer was a success.

16:57.184 --> 16:59.520
Meet the new you.

17:04.148 --> 17:06.068
Oh, my God.

17:06.234 --> 17:07.944
I'm...

17:08.112 --> 17:10.406
- I'm...
- What is it?

17:10.571 --> 17:13.909
Visual discrepancies?
Blurred vision? Haloing?

17:14.076 --> 17:16.244
I'm...I'm a fucking hunk.

17:17.621 --> 17:21.125
I take that you mean
your condition is satisfactory?

17:21.290 --> 17:22.835
Oh.

17:23.001 --> 17:25.045
Better than satisfactory.

17:26.422 --> 17:29.758
I feel...I feel healthy.

17:29.925 --> 17:32.761
Oh, it's been so long,
I'd forgotten what it's like.

17:34.388 --> 17:36.390
And my mind.

17:36.557 --> 17:38.267
Mmm.

17:45.816 --> 17:47.359
I've got my mind back.

17:47.526 --> 17:49.236
Oh, that little bastard
is finally gone.

17:49.403 --> 17:51.321
What little bastard?

17:52.406 --> 17:53.866
Never mind.

17:56.410 --> 17:57.786
Oh.

18:05.085 --> 18:08.172
Wow. This is what
all the fuss is about?

18:10.507 --> 18:12.384
I'm swinging one of these,

18:12.551 --> 18:14.887
now I'm just plain better
than every woman on the planet?

18:16.764 --> 18:18.640
I could get used to this.

18:21.685 --> 18:24.062
Ooh! Mmm. Ooh!

18:24.229 --> 18:25.481
Mmm.

18:25.647 --> 18:27.483
Sheesh.

18:27.649 --> 18:29.359
Doesn't take much
to get it excited.

18:29.526 --> 18:32.237
You'll have the rest of
your unnaturally long life

18:32.404 --> 18:33.697
struggling to avoid
all the trouble

18:33.864 --> 18:35.574
your new friend gets you into.

18:35.741 --> 18:38.327
But right now it's time
to follow through on our deal.

18:38.494 --> 18:40.579
You get rid of your leverage.

18:40.746 --> 18:42.873
Then we get rid of the old you.

18:59.097 --> 19:03.227
Snuffed out in our sleep
after such a valiant struggle.

19:03.393 --> 19:05.103
Sad.

19:05.270 --> 19:08.065
No, but here you are,
ready to carry the torch.

19:08.232 --> 19:09.942
It's not a...death.

19:10.108 --> 19:12.861
It's more like a rebirth.

19:13.028 --> 19:15.572
Still, I'd like
to do something for her.

19:17.032 --> 19:18.700
Send her out on a high note.

19:18.867 --> 19:21.495
And what exactly
did you have in mind?

19:21.662 --> 19:23.956
I need to take the new body
out for a test drive

19:24.122 --> 19:26.041
before you 86 the old one.

19:27.709 --> 19:29.419
God knows she could use a lay.

19:29.586 --> 19:33.215
Your narcissism
truly knows no bounds.

19:34.216 --> 19:36.718
After you've...finished,

19:36.885 --> 19:39.096
I expect you to hold up
your end of the bargain.

19:39.263 --> 19:42.057
Yeah, sure. Fine.
Whatever you want.

19:43.183 --> 19:45.310
Then, by all means, Olivia...

19:46.311 --> 19:48.772
..go fuck yourself.

19:57.698 --> 19:59.157
Olivia.

20:04.162 --> 20:06.123
Are you...

20:06.290 --> 20:08.041
Are we...

20:08.208 --> 20:09.960
Did it work?

20:10.127 --> 20:12.462
Mommy, you have no idea.

20:29.688 --> 20:31.106
Mmm!

20:31.273 --> 20:33.233
Mmm. Mmm.

20:33.400 --> 20:34.985
Ugh!

20:38.363 --> 20:39.948
What? What?

20:42.784 --> 20:45.162
However, comma, previous
experiments have resulted

20:45.329 --> 20:48.832
in spontaneous neural
decompensation, comma,

20:48.999 --> 20:52.127
possibly resulting in death,
which would be...

20:53.795 --> 20:56.632
..highly desirable
and cause for celebration.

20:58.759 --> 21:01.595
Don't listen to him.
It is a blemish. That's all.

21:01.762 --> 21:04.264
I'm not telling you anything
we didn't already know.

21:04.431 --> 21:06.058
I am not horrific!

21:06.224 --> 21:07.684
OK! I overstated the case,

21:07.851 --> 21:10.228
but, dear girl, you and I
both know you're not well.

21:10.395 --> 21:11.939
I warned you
that this would happen.

21:12.105 --> 21:14.691
Did you have a better idea
to keep me alive? No.

21:14.858 --> 21:16.234
Both of you, stop it.

21:16.401 --> 21:18.528
Johann, she is bat-shit crazy.

21:18.695 --> 21:21.156
'Crazy' is not a dispositive
term, medically speaking.

21:21.323 --> 21:23.158
She's arguing
with an imaginary friend.

21:23.325 --> 21:25.744
I'm pretty sure that qualifies
as crazy pretty much everywhere.

21:25.911 --> 21:28.872
I am still here, and you are
gonna treat me with respect,

21:29.039 --> 21:31.416
because without me,
you would not be me!

