catch a flight or a bullet.

40:18.250 --> 40:21.253
I didn't do anything to her.

40:22.463 --> 40:24.215
I swear.

40:27.468 --> 40:28.969
You're lying.

41:28.320 --> 41:30.823
Uncle Johann.

41:30.990 --> 41:35.619
Shelley, you have become
such a celebrity.

41:36.620 --> 41:38.789
Well, what are you doing here?

41:38.956 --> 41:40.499
I'm afraid
it's not a social call.

41:40.666 --> 41:42.793
It's...about your mother.

41:42.960 --> 41:46.463
Is she OK?
Roman told me she's sick.

41:46.630 --> 41:48.257
She is not at all well.

41:48.424 --> 41:51.093
If you see her coming, I need
you to call me immediately,

41:51.260 --> 41:54.763
and promise to get as far away
as you can, no matter what.

41:54.930 --> 41:56.765
Oh, my God.

41:56.932 --> 41:58.767
Is she gonna be OK?

41:58.934 --> 42:01.395
She's receiving state-of-the-art
medical attention,

42:01.562 --> 42:04.064
which I'm overseeing personally.

42:05.399 --> 42:07.776
Then she's in good hands.

42:07.943 --> 42:09.445
The best.

42:12.531 --> 42:14.325
Can you keep a secret?

42:19.455 --> 42:22.791
I'm leaving Hemlock Grove
tonight.

42:22.958 --> 42:27.630
This time tomorrow, I'll be
up in Maine chasing butterflies.

42:27.796 --> 42:32.259
I don't think it's safe for you
to be travelling all alone.

42:33.469 --> 42:35.137
Can you keep another secret?

42:35.304 --> 42:37.973
Sometimes I fear
that's all I'm good at.

42:39.016 --> 42:41.393
I have a boyfriend.

42:44.230 --> 42:46.190
Now that you're here,
I'll introduce you.

42:46.357 --> 42:48.943
I already know you'll get along.
Aitor gets along with everybody.

42:49.109 --> 42:51.695
You are truly full of surprises.

42:51.862 --> 42:55.491
I am...so happy for you,
Shelley.

42:55.658 --> 42:57.159
Truly happy.

42:58.494 --> 43:00.162
Can I share a secret of my own?

43:00.329 --> 43:01.997
Do tell.

43:02.164 --> 43:05.584
I've been
seeing someone myself.

43:05.751 --> 43:07.503
What's he like?

43:15.344 --> 43:16.929
It feels...

43:20.933 --> 43:23.018
I don't know how to describe it.

43:24.436 --> 43:26.897
Like you can be your ideal self

43:27.064 --> 43:31.443
because that's what he sees
when he looks at you.

43:32.945 --> 43:34.989
What am I going to do
without you?

43:35.155 --> 43:36.907
Write...

43:38.534 --> 43:40.160
..every day.

43:45.666 --> 43:47.584
Well...

43:49.211 --> 43:52.548
Well, where is
your special someone?

43:52.715 --> 43:56.010
I can't wait to meet him.

44:09.189 --> 44:10.691
I almost believed him.

44:13.360 --> 44:17.072
He was a good liar,
but he got what he deserved.

44:18.407 --> 44:21.243
Still, Destiny's dead
because of me.

44:28.000 --> 44:30.044
Edge Cliff Woods.

44:31.045 --> 44:33.630
Told me his guys
were gonna bury us there.

45:07.831 --> 45:09.958
I swear
I didn't make him up.

45:10.125 --> 45:12.002
No, I don't think Aitor Quantic

45:12.169 --> 45:14.463
is something anybody
could make up.

45:17.257 --> 45:18.759
There he is.

45:20.302 --> 45:23.639
- Story time.
- You're gonna love this.

45:23.806 --> 45:28.602
This is a story about a man
and three wishes.

45:30.479 --> 45:34.858
There's no genie,
but there is a bottle,

45:35.025 --> 45:37.778
because our man
was a drinking man.

45:37.945 --> 45:40.572
Yeah.

45:40.739 --> 45:42.241
And one night, he found himself

45:42.408 --> 45:46.328
face to face
with one of his darkest fears.

45:46.495 --> 45:48.789
This particular bottle

45:48.956 --> 45:52.793
that had given him so much joy
and pleasure was empty.

45:54.420 --> 45:56.713
In fact, there wasn't
a drop left in the whole house.

45:56.880 --> 45:59.508
And no money to buy more.

46:00.509 --> 46:02.845
That's when he made
his first wish.

46:03.846 --> 46:08.600
He summoned all the powers
from realms seen and unseen

46:08.767 --> 46:10.602
and wished for another bottle.

46:10.769 --> 46:12.521
Yeah.

46:12.688 --> 46:14.690
- Alright.
- Yeah.

46:14.857 --> 46:17.985
And when he opened his eyes,
he saw all the empty bottles

46:18.152 --> 46:22.614
lying around and realised
his wish had been granted.

46:22.781 --> 46:26.326
He could take 'em to the store,
collect the deposit money,

46:26.493 --> 46:28.787
and buy more booze.

46:32.875 --> 46:34.543
So he jumped in his truck.

46:34.710 --> 46:36.837
He hauled ass out of there,

46:37.004 --> 46:39.840
but he didn't check
the rear-view as he backed up.

46:40.007 --> 46:43.844
So he didn't see what made
the loud and terrible thunk

46:44.011 --> 46:46.680
he heard
when the truck rolled over it.

46:52.352 --> 46:54.396
Made his second wish.

46:55.939 --> 46:59.234
Summoned those powers,
from realms seen and unseen.

46:59.401 --> 47:04.448
"Please, please, please, don't
let it be the neighbour's dog."

47:06.200 --> 47:08.494
And lo and behold,
his wish was granted.

47:09.786 --> 47:11.747
It wasn't the neighbour's dog.

47:11.914 --> 47:15.626
It was an old man,
just walking by.

47:21.381 --> 47:24.551
The cause of death, tyre tracks
on or about the head.

47:31.183 --> 47:35.771
I went to jail
for vehicular homicide.

47:36.855 --> 47:40.234
I did my time,
but when I was released,

47:40.400 --> 47:43.028
I thought I knew more
than the authorities,

47:43.195 --> 47:45.280
so I skipped out on parole.

47:45.447 --> 47:47.991
I was still suffering
from that disease of self

47:48.158 --> 47:50.369
that got me drinking
in the first place.

47:51.912 --> 47:53.997
I've been a fugitive ever since.

47:56.833 --> 47:59.545
Now, this former drinking man,

47:59.711 --> 48:01.296
this me...

48:02.798 --> 48:04.508
..made a third wish.

48:06.677 --> 48:11.098
I wished for something so rare,
so impossible,

48:11.265 --> 48:13.976
the odds of me finding it
were due south of none...

48:14.977 --> 48:18.564
..all the powers from realms
seen and unseen notwithstanding.

48:21.817 --> 48:23.527
I wished for a soul mate.

48:25.904 --> 48:28.407
And a woman so rare,

48:28.574 --> 48:32.953
so beautiful and unique
came unto me...

48:34.121 --> 48:37.291
..causing me to say,
"What's up?"

48:41.628 --> 48:45.173
I, uh...asked her
to come away with me.

48:46.174 --> 48:48.093
To run away
would be more accurate,

48:48.260 --> 48:49.845
'cause I can't stay here.

48:50.012 --> 48:52.556
I'm afraid of being caught
for what I did.

48:52.723 --> 48:56.310
That's my disease of self
rearing its ugly head

48:56.476 --> 48:59.771
because...because what I
was really asking her to do

48:59.938 --> 49:02.399
was hide herself from the world.

49:03.400 --> 49:05.360
She's already
done enough hiding.

49:05.527 --> 49:07.321
It wouldn't be fair.

49:08.322 --> 49:10.282
I wish things
could be different...

49:12.743 --> 49:14.536
..but I'm all out of wishes.

49:24.963 --> 49:29.468
So, with this siren song
as my swan song...

49:30.886 --> 49:32.596
..I bid you all adieu.

49:38.143 --> 49:39.436
We should get out of here.

49:39.603 --> 49:42.397
Don't go! I love you.

49:43.607 --> 49:45.233
<i>Stay where you are!</i>

49:45.400 --> 49:48.779
<i>Please, do not run!
I repeat, do not run!</i>

50:42.791 --> 50:44.292
What? It's late.

50:44.459 --> 50:46.962
- Uh, Roman Godfrey?
- Who is this?

50:47.129 --> 50:49.631
Yeah, hi.
This is Detective Israel.

50:49.798 --> 50:51.133
I'm hoping you can help me

50:51.299 --> 50:53.343
with an ongoing
homicide investigation.

50:53.510 --> 50:54.886
I'm following up on a lead

50:55.053 --> 50:57.431
regarding the murder
of Merrill Samis and his family.

50:57.597 --> 51:01.435
They were found frozen to death
in South Erie last week.

51:01.601 --> 51:03.061
I don't even know who that is.

51:03.228 --> 51:05.897
If this is some kind of a
prank call, I'm not in the mood.

51:06.064 --> 51:07.315
"Helmet smorgasbord."

51:07.482 --> 51:09.151
Does that mean anything to you?

51:11.319 --> 51:14.990
Mr Samis texted that
to your phone the day he died.

51:15.157 --> 51:17.033
Where'd you say
you were calling from?

51:17.200 --> 51:19.494
South Erie.

51:31.798 --> 51:33.508
Blinsky!

51:33.675 --> 51:35.218
I wasn't sleeping.

51:35.385 --> 51:36.762
You weren't answering
your phone, either.

51:36.928 --> 51:38.638
Erie. Erie, Pennsylvania.

51:38.805 --> 51:40.474
That's where we need
to be looking.

51:42.184 --> 51:44.227
Put it in the fucking computer!

51:44.394 --> 51:47.189
Even with a zipcode
this would take a while.

52:00.911 --> 52:04.289
We got him. We fucking got him!

53:04.307 --> 53:05.976
I'm looking for some protection.

53:06.977 --> 53:08.562
Oh, we're fresh out of condoms.

53:08.728 --> 53:10.730
Try holding an aspirin
between your knees.

53:10.897 --> 53:13.900
I live alone, and there
have been some break-ins

53:14.067 --> 53:15.569
in my neighbourhood.

53:17.028 --> 53:18.989
Say no more.

53:19.155 --> 53:20.490
Just so happens we're having

53:20.657 --> 53:22.742
a 'World's Gone to Shit' special
this week.

53:22.909 --> 53:26.746
For the ladies,
the Taurus.45/.41.

53:26.913 --> 53:28.832
Great conceal and carry.

53:28.999 --> 53:31.835
The Smith & Wesson M&P22.

53:32.961 --> 53:36.464
And the Sig Sauer P226.

53:36.631 --> 53:38.717
All available
in breast-cancer pink.

53:38.884 --> 53:40.552
Mm.

53:40.719 --> 53:43.889
I was thinking more along
the lines of a Desert Eagle.

53:44.055 --> 53:46.558
Recoil on a weapon
like that'll land you

53:46.725 --> 53:49.102
on your pretty little bubble
butt back in last Tuesday.

53:50.353 --> 53:53.481
You guys didn't think
my pretty little bubble butt

53:53.648 --> 53:56.818
was so helpless
when we were dropped in the LZ,

53:56.985 --> 54:00.614
to patch up Chosen Company,
2nd Battalion,

54:00.780 --> 54:02.532
after the Battle of Wanat.

54:02.699 --> 54:07.495
"God's own angels,"
I think the GIs called us.

54:09.205 --> 54:10.999
Sorry about the jokes.

54:11.166 --> 54:12.751
It's alright.

54:12.918 --> 54:14.920
Nothing I haven't heard before.

54:23.803 --> 54:25.347
Need some hollow points.

54:25.513 --> 54:29.017
125 grain. Jacketed.

54:29.184 --> 54:32.854
Jesus. What kind of burglars
are we talking about here?

54:33.021 --> 54:37.400
The kind you drop fast,
and they don't get up.

55:48.054 --> 55:51.391
♪ That girl sweet
as the cane in the Malibu rum

55:51.558 --> 55:54.811
♪ With a mouth full of smiles
like 12 million suns

55:54.978 --> 55:58.189
♪ But go messin' with her, son,
she'll put you in check

55:58.356 --> 56:01.693
♪ With your ass in the air
and a boot on your neck

56:01.860 --> 56:04.946
♪ Rebel Breezy ain't scared
She just throwing it down

56:05.113 --> 56:08.408
♪ So you best come correct
or get run out of town

56:08.575 --> 56:10.160
♪ 'Cause she swung like a G

56:10.326 --> 56:11.828
♪ On you and your set

56:11.995 --> 56:13.371
♪ Over, under don't matter

56:13.538 --> 56:14.914
♪ 'Cause you lost the bet

56:15.081 --> 56:17.751
♪ She planks so good
She planks so hard

56:17.917 --> 56:21.546
♪ Gotta plank like her
or we both go cold

56:21.713 --> 56:23.506
♪ We be plankin' too... ♪

